  "body": "From https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/2691#issuecomment-752231692\r\n\r\nCustom chains may allow deploying contracts bigger than 24 kB but the limit is currently hard-coded in the compiler and exceeding it triggers a warning that can't be suppressed. In #2691 it was proposed that the solution might be to introduce a compiler flag that allows the user to change the limit to an arbitrary value and avoid the warning.",
